Well studies show that the origin of Arabs are from the levantine desert as Yemen had already a lot of kingdoms which spoke languages like Himyarite, Sabaic and hadramic until the rise of Islam when Arabic replaced all of them. Jazan region was also not part of Yemen but an autonomous tribal entity under the Ottoman Empire + the clothes worn in the video they belong to the tribes of Khawlan only, not all Yemenis dress like this

Hello:
If you look at these people customs , You will see a similarity with the people of Hawaii , The way they welcome the guest with
flowers around the head and the way the men dressed , Both they wear a skirt . The name Hawaii came from Arabic means
the breasy Island . The People of Yemen like the rest in the Area liked diving and looking for pearls , The word in Arabic for pearls
